                  <summary><p>This manuscript of the <title xml:lang="sa">Vṛddhahārītasmṛti</title> is the third in a <ref target="Sanscrit_0808.xml">collection</ref> of five <term xml:lang="sa">smṛti</term> texts. The scribe has left empty spaces, sometimes filled with dots, which seem to represent illegible or damaged spans of texts in the antigraph that he was copying from. This manuscript breaks off at verse 330 of the sixth <term xml:lang="sa">adhyāya</term> (ed. Shastri et al., <ref target="https://archive.org/details/smriti-sandarbha-gurumandal-series/Smriti%20Sandarbha%20Part%202%20-%20Gurumandal%20Series%201952/page/n618/mode/1up">1159</ref>), although it is not clear whether there are missing folios at the end.</p>
</summary>
                  
